    "type": "Introduction",
    "title": "Consonants: Palate Sounds (चवर्ग)",
    "description": "In this episode, we learn the palatal consonants — sounds made by pressing the tongue against the palate (roof of the mouth). These five letters are च, छ, ज, झ, and ञ. You'll also learn common words that use these sounds.",
    "keyPoints": [
      "च (cha), छ (chha), ज (ja), झ (jha), ञ (nya) — the palatal group",
      "These sounds are produced with the middle of the tongue touching the hard palate",
      "छ is the aspirated version of च, and झ is the aspirated version of ज",
      "ञ is rare on its own but appears in conjuncts like ज्ञ"
    ]
  },
